00:21:21,360 --> 00:21:24,720
Your Honor, look at this list of complaints.

243
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:27,560
And I quote you directly, sir, when I say--

244
00:21:39,440 --> 00:21:43,440
Gee, sir, I thought you only got
contempt of court for opening your mouth.

245
00:21:45,760 --> 00:21:47,960
Mahoney, I'm warning you.

246
00:21:48,120 --> 00:21:51,160
You keep Lassard's C.O.Ps
out of my precinct.

247
00:21:51,240 --> 00:21:53,040
You don't understand
what I'm trying to do.

248
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:55,360
I understand
exactly what you're trying to do.

249
00:21:55,400 --> 00:21:58,840
Just keep them out,
especially these two little buttwads.

250
00:21:58,960 --> 00:22:01,440
Excuse me, sir,
but you're not planning to attack us...

251
00:22:01,560 --> 00:22:04,200
with any more of your bodily functions,
are you?

252
00:22:06,520 --> 00:22:10,640
You just make sure
that we never meet again. Ever.

253
00:22:12,360 --> 00:22:15,600
You know, with those two idiots
in Lassard's program, it'll never work.

254
00:22:41,920 --> 00:22:43,400
Excuse me, sir.

255
00:22:43,560 --> 00:22:45,600
We're looking for a Mrs. Feldman.

256
00:22:45,720 --> 00:22:47,520
-Do you know her?
-Yes.

257
00:22:55,440 --> 00:22:58,120
Excuse me, ma'am.
Do you know a Mrs. Lois--

258
00:22:58,200 --> 00:23:01,000
-Where can we find Lois Feldman, please?
-There.

259
00:23:01,920 --> 00:23:03,040
Thank you.

260
00:23:09,440 --> 00:23:10,720
Mrs. Feldman?

261
00:23:10,840 --> 00:23:12,520
-Who's asking?
-Police.

262
00:23:13,320 --> 00:23:15,520
Is it about those damn library books?

263
00:23:16,720 --> 00:23:20,960
We're following up on your alleged
interest in the Citizens On Patrol program.

264
00:23:21,720 --> 00:23:24,560
Then I'm Mrs. Feldman. Come on in.

265
00:23:26,520 --> 00:23:28,640
Callahan, cover your rear.

266
00:23:39,760 --> 00:23:41,840
I admire your taste.

267
00:23:41,960 --> 00:23:45,800
Yes, well, I do all my own decorating.

268
00:23:47,040 --> 00:23:48,840
You have a talent for it, ma'am.

269
00:23:48,960 --> 00:23:51,040
I'll be with you in a moment, Sarge.

270
00:23:51,440 --> 00:23:54,560
Perhaps you'd like to discuss
the program first, ma'am.

271
00:23:54,600 --> 00:23:56,120
What's to discuss?

272
00:23:56,120 --> 00:23:59,640
Think I want to hang out here
and listen to arteries hardening?

273
00:23:59,960 --> 00:24:02,000
Where did I put that bulletproof vest?

274
00:24:15,560 --> 00:24:18,840
All right, fall in! Come on, please, line up.

275
00:24:18,920 --> 00:24:21,200
Come on, I need a lineup here.

276
00:24:21,360 --> 00:24:23,400
Hello, ma'am. Ladies and gentlemen--

277
00:24:28,160 --> 00:24:30,960
-Thank you, Miss....
-Mrs. Feldman.

278
00:24:51,360 --> 00:24:54,120
I want to welcome all of you
to the Academy.

279
00:24:54,360 --> 00:24:58,800
You are part of a new
and exciting program that I call...

280
00:24:59,920 --> 00:25:01,360
-C.O.P.
-C.O.P.

281
00:25:03,560 --> 00:25:06,440
-Citizens On Patrol.
-Citizens On Patrol.

282
00:25:06,840 --> 00:25:09,520
-Citizens On Patrol!
-Citizens On Patrol!

283
00:25:10,840 --> 00:25:13,320
You will work and train with the police.

284
00:25:13,560 --> 00:25:15,920
The police will work and train with you.

285
00:25:16,160 --> 00:25:19,640
Working and training,
training and working.

286
00:25:19,920 --> 00:25:21,400
Excuse me, Commandant.

287
00:25:21,560 --> 00:25:24,840
But do you expect the community
to do the job of the police force?

288
00:25:24,960 --> 00:25:28,960
There are many, many jobs
for many, many people.

289
00:25:29,520 --> 00:25:31,560
Sir, I'll take care of this.

290
00:25:32,120 --> 00:25:34,600
Excuse me, young lady,
what the Commandant means...

291
00:25:34,720 --> 00:25:37,440
is that this program
will promote understanding...

292
00:25:37,560 --> 00:25:39,120
between the community and the police...

293
00:25:39,240 --> 00:25:42,560
and make the community
more active in crime prevention.

294
00:25:43,120 --> 00:25:46,520
Active in crime prevention?
Won't that be dangerous?

295
00:25:46,640 --> 00:25:49,720
No. We just want to teach citizens...

296
00:25:49,800 --> 00:25:52,000
to prevent crimes from taking place.

297
00:25:52,160 --> 00:25:56,240
It sounds fine in theory.
Let's hope it works in practice.

298
00:25:59,560 --> 00:26:02,000
I like him. He's a really nice fish.

299
00:26:02,720 --> 00:26:04,440
He looks a little like you.

300
00:26:07,240 --> 00:26:10,640
I will attend
an international police seminar in London.

301
00:26:10,760 --> 00:26:14,120
It would be
the crowning achievement of my career...

302
00:26:14,640 --> 00:26:16,400
if I could close this seminar...

303
00:26:16,560 --> 00:26:19,600
by bringing instructors
from all around the world...

304
00:26:19,720 --> 00:26:23,960
here to watch
the C.O.P. program in action.

305
00:26:24,800 --> 00:26:29,160
I'm counting on all of you
to make that possible.

306
00:26:29,200 --> 00:26:31,400
In Comdt. Lassard's absence...

307
00:26:31,520 --> 00:26:35,040
I've appointed a very able-bodied
and experienced officer...

308
00:26:35,120 --> 00:26:36,560
to run the Academy.

309
00:26:37,640 --> 00:26:40,000
Perfect timing. Here he is now.

310
00:26:42,160 --> 00:26:43,560
Attention!

311
00:26:55,360 --> 00:26:57,840
Two weeks of Harris? Damn!

312
00:27:03,560 --> 00:27:04,600
Damn.

313
00:27:05,760 --> 00:27:07,320
Deodorant? Thanks.

314
00:27:14,320 --> 00:27:15,640
Straighten this mess up.

315
00:27:15,720 --> 00:27:17,200
-What mess?
-Now!

316
00:27:17,960 --> 00:27:20,840
I want all of you dirtbags
and that group of C.O.P. people...

317
00:27:20,920 --> 00:27:23,640
out in front of this dormitory
at 1400 hours.

318
00:27:24,160 --> 00:27:25,840
Move it!

319
00:27:25,960 --> 00:27:29,000
Sir, we were just commenting
on how you'd mellowed.

320
00:27:31,440 --> 00:27:34,320
-Captain?
-What is it, Mahoney?

321
00:27:34,440 --> 00:27:36,760
I hope you're gonna
give this program a fair chance.

322
00:27:36,800 --> 00:27:41,040
This program, Mahoney,
is just like you: a bad idea.

323
00:27:41,160 --> 00:27:42,720
That's your opinion, sir.

324
00:27:42,840 --> 00:27:45,840
But this is Comdt. Lassard's idea,
and his Academy.

325
00:27:48,040 --> 00:27:50,000
Things can change, Mahoney.

326
00:27:50,760 --> 00:27:53,360
Yes, things can change.

327
00:27:53,640 --> 00:27:55,560
I'll see you out front.

328
00:28:11,240 --> 00:28:13,160
I bet that was refreshing, sir.

329
00:28:15,600 --> 00:28:17,400
Over the next two weeks...

330
00:28:17,520 --> 00:28:20,840
you'll go through
a modified training program.

331
00:28:21,000 --> 00:28:24,360
You'll learn many, many keys
to crime prevention.

332
00:28:24,960 --> 00:28:28,920
Keys you can teach many, many others
in your community.

333
00:28:29,040 --> 00:28:32,920
Modified? Modified nothing.
I want the works.

334
00:28:33,040 --> 00:28:34,720
-Yeah.
-Madam...

335
00:28:34,800 --> 00:28:37,840
I think it's time for a dose of reality.

336
00:28:38,520 --> 00:28:40,600
You can forget Lassard's hype.

337
00:28:42,120 --> 00:28:45,640
You people do not belong here.

338
00:28:46,600 --> 00:28:49,640
Especially you and you.

339
00:28:53,600 --> 00:28:57,440
Community action groups mean one thing,
and one thing only.

340
00:29:00,320 --> 00:29:02,240
I hope that wasn't gum.

341
00:29:05,640 --> 00:29:07,560
You heard the Captain. Is it?

342
00:29:08,560 --> 00:29:12,240
It's definitely gum, sir. Bubble gum.
Cherry, I think.

343
00:29:12,720 --> 00:29:15,400
-Thank you, Proctor.
-You're welcome, sir.

344
00:29:18,200 --> 00:29:21,960
These groups only mean
citizens getting in the way of the police.

345
00:29:22,000 --> 00:29:24,320
Now, I don't get involved
in your business...

346
00:29:24,440 --> 00:29:27,200
and I don't want you involved in my--

347
00:29:30,920 --> 00:29:32,320
Now, if you were smart...

348
00:29:32,320 --> 00:29:36,000
you would go home
and forget this stupid idea....

349
00:29:38,440 --> 00:29:40,640
Are those wedding bells I hear, sir?

350
00:29:45,040 --> 00:29:48,920
-Whose damn mutt is this?
-It's my damn mutt.

351
00:29:50,240 --> 00:29:52,840
I want him out of here!

352
00:29:52,960 --> 00:29:55,040
-But, sir--
-Out!

353
00:29:58,200 --> 00:30:02,040
I am not getting rid of Clarence.
He's my pet.

354
00:30:02,320 --> 00:30:05,800
Why should you?
After all, Harris has Proctor.

355
00:30:06,440 --> 00:30:07,800
I'll take him.

356
00:30:08,240 --> 00:30:10,400
I have a big house, nice yard.

357
00:30:11,240 --> 00:30:13,840
See, he likes me. We'll get along fine.

358
00:30:13,960 --> 00:30:16,040
Me, too? I'm housebroken.

359
00:30:17,160 --> 00:30:19,760
Come on, C.O.Ps,
let's step up to the white line!

360
00:30:19,840 --> 00:30:23,160
Let's line ourselves up with a slot,
then let's listen to Mr. Jones.

361
00:30:23,200 --> 00:30:25,120
Thank you, Sgt. Tackleberry.

362
00:30:26,840 --> 00:30:29,920
This is a standard police issue.38.

363
00:30:30,320 --> 00:30:32,240
Examine this weapon carefully.

364
00:30:32,360 --> 00:30:34,440
You must be sure
this weapon is not loaded.

365
00:30:34,560 --> 00:30:38,720
You will be responsible for the loading
and unloading of this weapon yourself.

366
00:30:38,960 --> 00:30:40,840
Now, Sgt. Tackleberry.

367
00:30:43,600 --> 00:30:46,040
You want to become one with the gun.

368
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:51,720
Feel the gun, caress the gun...

369
00:30:53,520 --> 00:30:56,800
until it's a living, breathing, vibrating...

370
00:30:57,040 --> 00:31:00,120
extension of yourself.

371
00:31:00,200 --> 00:31:01,840
I look for the same in a woman.

372
00:31:01,960 --> 00:31:03,800
This sucker's not loaded.

373
00:31:04,160 --> 00:31:05,960
You won't be using live ammo.

374
00:31:06,520 --> 00:31:10,800
Tack, how about letting me squeeze off
a few rounds of that baby?

375
00:31:10,920 --> 00:31:12,320
Tack?

376
00:31:13,360 --> 00:31:14,920
Affirmative, Mrs. F.

377
00:31:17,040 --> 00:31:20,000
Now, be careful
because a.44 magnum has quite a...

378
00:31:22,560 --> 00:31:23,520
kick.

379
00:31:23,800 --> 00:31:25,440
Damn, that was fun!

380
00:31:29,960 --> 00:31:31,800
Rescuing the drowning victim.

381
00:31:31,920 --> 00:31:34,800
Now, when approaching
a potentially dangerous...

382
00:31:34,920 --> 00:31:37,120
and out-of-control victim,
use this stroke only.

383
00:31:37,240 --> 00:31:38,920
Arms out of the way for protection.

384
00:31:39,040 --> 00:31:42,720
Now, when you get the victim in control,
you slip your arm across his chest...

385
00:31:42,840 --> 00:31:44,240
under his opposite arm.

386
00:31:44,360 --> 00:31:46,720
Rest his head and his neck
against your shoulder.

387
00:31:46,840 --> 00:31:50,240
Kick with your feet.
Now, your victim could be struggling.

388
00:31:50,640 --> 00:31:53,600
Struggle, House. Good, House....

389
00:31:53,960 --> 00:31:54,920
House!

390
00:32:03,720 --> 00:32:05,760
Really swift! I'll get him!

391
00:32:10,320 --> 00:32:13,960
Arnie, get out of the pool! You just ate!

392
00:32:30,200 --> 00:32:31,840
Get him out of here!

393
00:32:35,520 --> 00:32:36,920
Thanks, pal.

394
00:32:38,560 --> 00:32:41,840
Now we have an opportunity
to start our water safety lesson.

395
00:32:44,600 --> 00:32:46,640
I will play the drowning victim.

396
00:33:01,040 --> 00:33:03,000
Now, who's going to save me?

397
00:33:03,120 --> 00:33:04,760
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

398
00:33:34,520 --> 00:33:37,800
That was mighty brave. I admire that.

399
00:33:38,400 --> 00:33:39,840
That was nothing.

400
00:33:40,600 --> 00:33:44,120
You don't have a hair dryer,
or perhaps some mousse?

401
00:33:44,760 --> 00:33:48,400
No. Your hair looks nice. It's very stylish.

402
00:33:48,800 --> 00:33:50,720
Moi?
Stylish?

403
00:33:52,760 --> 00:33:54,640
I think I'd better be going.

404
00:33:54,800 --> 00:33:56,200
Mickey!

405
00:33:58,000 --> 00:34:00,160
He's dead! He killed him!

406
00:34:00,720 --> 00:34:04,320
-I'm sure the Academy will pay for it.
-What about the sentimental value?

407
00:34:04,400 --> 00:34:06,320
This is a family heirloom here.

408
00:34:06,440 --> 00:34:09,800
This is the last thing I ever stole
before joining the Academy.

409
00:34:09,920 --> 00:34:13,600
What the hell is this? Cadets in heat?

410
00:34:13,760 --> 00:34:15,400
No. We were just, like, talking.

411
00:34:15,520 --> 00:34:18,120
Just, like, talk somewhere else.

412
00:34:18,400 --> 00:34:21,320
This is not a spawning pool.
I want discipline.

413
00:34:21,720 --> 00:34:23,760
Do I make myself clear, Zed?

414
00:34:24,320 --> 00:34:25,640
Discipline!

415
00:34:27,160 --> 00:34:28,720
-Jerk.
-What?

416
00:34:28,960 --> 00:34:30,360
He said bye.

417
00:34:33,400 --> 00:34:36,640
No. I said jerk. I think it was pretty clear.

418
00:34:36,760 --> 00:34:38,440
-I said, "Jerk."
-Jerk.

419
00:35:14,360 --> 00:35:16,320
Cadets, I'd now like to discuss with you...

420
00:35:16,440 --> 00:35:18,640
something that will be
vital for you to know...

421
00:35:18,760 --> 00:35:22,200
when you're, like, out there on the job
as a police officer.

422
00:35:22,320 --> 00:35:25,160
And that's the correct way
to eat a doughnut.

423
00:35:25,800 --> 00:35:28,040
-A doughnut--
-Attention!

424
00:35:29,840 --> 00:35:31,240
Capt. Harris.

425
00:35:39,520 --> 00:35:43,560
From this moment on, anyone
who misplaces their canister of Mace...

426
00:35:43,560 --> 00:35:45,640
will be reprimanded and fined.

427
00:35:45,760 --> 00:35:47,960
-Is that clear?
-Yes, sir!

428
00:35:56,600 --> 00:35:57,600
Bye.

429
00:36:00,720 --> 00:36:02,640
As Citizens On Patrol...

430
00:36:02,760 --> 00:36:06,120
endurance and longevity
should be very important to you.

431
00:36:06,800 --> 00:36:10,200
Aerobic activity will keep you in shape...

432
00:36:11,000 --> 00:36:12,800
and keep that heart rate up.

433
00:36:13,200 --> 00:36:16,000
Music, however,
makes it a little less painful.

434
00:36:16,400 --> 00:36:18,440
Hooks, cassette.

435
00:36:18,600 --> 00:36:21,840
I have confidence that Sgt. Hooks
has chosen the appropriate music.

436
00:36:21,960 --> 00:36:23,360
No cassette.

437
00:36:23,520 --> 00:36:24,840
Let's go.

438
00:36:29,000 --> 00:36:31,440
Nice selection, Hooks. All right.

439
00:36:31,560 --> 00:36:34,600
Slow walk. Slow start.

440
00:36:35,320 --> 00:36:37,760
Keep your arms moving. That's good.

441
00:36:37,920 --> 00:36:40,240
Into a nice slow jog. Okay!

442
00:36:40,800 --> 00:36:44,040
Arms moving. Keep breathing.
Don't forget to breathe.

443
00:36:44,120 --> 00:36:47,760
Tuck his tummy, Hooks. Attagirl. Let's go.

444
00:37:01,920 --> 00:37:05,320
Now, this whistle can be very valuable...

445
00:37:05,440 --> 00:37:07,800
when walking through
a bad neighborhood.

446
00:37:07,960 --> 00:37:10,720
If your purse gets snatched,
blow this whistle...

447
00:37:11,000 --> 00:37:14,240
to alert your neighbors and the police
so they can help.

448
00:37:14,360 --> 00:37:16,960
Now, Mrs. Feldman,
would you play the victim?

449
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:21,000
-Yes.
-Okay, and I'll be Mr. Purse Snatcher.

450
00:37:21,120 --> 00:37:23,840
-Okay.
-Go.

451
00:37:37,960 --> 00:37:39,360
Any questions?

452
00:38:00,320 --> 00:38:02,400
Now, practice.

453
00:38:14,160 --> 00:38:17,800
You had him for, like, a minute.
He was scared. He was, like, flinching.

454
00:38:17,920 --> 00:38:19,400
His face went....

455
00:38:49,960 --> 00:38:51,040
Sorry.

456
00:38:52,440 --> 00:38:55,920
Citizens On Patrol. What a joke.

457
00:38:56,320 --> 00:38:59,600
-You know what C.O.P. really stands for?
-No, sir. What?

458
00:38:59,720 --> 00:39:02,920
-Collection Of Pissants. That's not funny.
-No, sir.

459
00:39:03,040 --> 00:39:07,320
This citizen-action crap is a disaster,
a bad idea, and I'm going to prove it.

460
00:39:07,320 --> 00:39:08,520
Yes, sir.

461
00:39:11,760 --> 00:39:15,000
Excuse me, everyone.

462
00:39:15,120 --> 00:39:16,440
I mean, not everyone.

463
00:39:16,560 --> 00:39:19,800
Attention! Excuse me. Move it!

464
00:39:20,440 --> 00:39:23,440
-Everybody, come over here!
-Hooks.

465
00:39:23,720 --> 00:39:27,960
Stop embarrassing the Police Department
and join your civilian buddies.

466
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:31,120
May I have your attention, please?
Hooks, the tank!

467
00:39:32,400 --> 00:39:35,120
-I'm so sorry.
-You dimwit!

468
00:39:40,160 --> 00:39:42,400
Today, Hooks, today.

469
00:39:49,000 --> 00:39:52,800
Now, take your little munchkin voice
and go away.

470
00:39:57,200 --> 00:39:58,560
Listen up!

471
00:39:58,960 --> 00:40:03,360
This is the proper procedure
for administering oxygen.

472
00:40:04,320 --> 00:40:08,200
You place the mask securely
about the face of the patient...

473
00:40:08,320 --> 00:40:10,640
and then have them breathe deeply.

474
00:40:15,160 --> 00:40:18,440
Now, that is the way it's done
in Capt. Harris' precinct.

475
00:40:19,720 --> 00:40:22,560
What the hell? Hooks!

476
00:40:29,160 --> 00:40:31,920
So you gentlemen think
you're on a vacation?

477
00:40:32,320 --> 00:40:35,560
You're no better than anyone else,
so let's go, let's get to work.

478
00:40:35,600 --> 00:40:37,520
Come on, dudes, chill out.

479
00:40:38,360 --> 00:40:41,360
You dudes are setting a bad example.

480
00:40:42,040 --> 00:40:45,600
Can't hear you, bro. Can't you see
I'm getting my beauty sleep?

481
00:40:45,760 --> 00:40:47,000
I'm sorry.

482
00:40:47,720 --> 00:40:48,800
Move it!

483
00:40:52,800 --> 00:40:54,400
You sure told them.

484
00:40:56,160 --> 00:40:59,040
Did you ever think about
maybe getting some contact lenses...

485
00:40:59,160 --> 00:41:01,240
or something, like, you know?

486
00:41:02,200 --> 00:41:03,720
You'd look good in them.

487
00:41:05,920 --> 00:41:08,000
Proctor, this is an alley.

488
00:41:08,120 --> 00:41:10,720
I know, sir, but these are the directions
Mahoney gave me.

489
00:41:10,720 --> 00:41:11,720
-Mahoney?
-Yes, sir.

490
00:41:11,800 --> 00:41:14,240
He says this restaurant
